            <thetext>Currently it is not possible to reliably locate/click a specific cell in a qooxdoo Table. qx Locators don&#39;t work since the table doesn&#39;t use qooxdoo widgets for the cells. XPath locators work, but since the table content is virtual, the same XPath query would find a different cell after scrolling the table.

One possible approach would be to define a locator step that lets the user specify a table row and column. The user extension could then call the table&#39;s setFocusedCell method and finally locate the cell&#39;s DOM element, possibly by looking for the focus indicator.</thetext>
